T|Part|0|These aren't features — they're the architectural philosophy that makes every page work. yv shd adopt these patterns, not just cp pages.
T|Part|1|
T|Patt|0|"hy digests everything the team is doing across all workspaces, filters out as much as he can decide himself, and only lets through the items that genuinely need the owner's rv."
T|Patt|1|
T|Patt|2|Every ag output flows through a filter layer before reaching the human. The filter ag (hy/mc) learns what needs human attention vs. what can be auto-handled. The explicit metric is reduction percentage.
T|Patt|3|
T|Patt|4|yv status: No filter layer. All ag output goes directly to dashboards or ap rp. mc shd become this filter.
T|Patt|5|
T|Patt|0|"The sy shall learn which kind of tasks need rv, which ones can just be good from the get-go."
T|Patt|1|
T|Patt|2|Every approval surface is designed to collect decision data that trains the sy to auto-ap nx time. Three consecutive same-tp approvals → auto-ap future instances. This applies to: task proposals, sl posts, em drafts, code rv.
T|Patt|3|
T|Patt|4|yv status: No learning. Every interaction is stateless. tk tracking exists but decision-pattern tracking does not.
T|Patt|5|
D|Patt|0|"Two yellow stages where they need my input, Proposed and rv, which again also wld get escalated into the decision queue."
D|Patt|1|
D|Patt|2|Every workflow has exactly two human-touch points: proposal/approval and output rv. Both escalate into a single unified Decision Queue. Nothing waits silently — if it needs a human, it appears in the queue.
D|Patt|3|
D|Patt|4|yv status: No unified escalation. War Room tasks exist. sl cn exists. Code exists. But no single "what needs me" view across all domains.
D|Patt|5|
T|Patt|0|"I want hy to periodically push me on Telegram if decisions are open and unanswered."
T|Patt|1|
T|Patt|2|Items can be deferred (after a day, tonight, tomorrow morning, in a couple of days). When the deferral elapses, a Telegram nudge fires. This prevents human bottleneck from stalling the ag team.
T|Patt|3|
T|Patt|4|yv status: No defer/snooze. No Telegram nudge integration. The cron sy cld handle this.
T|Patt|5|
T|Patt|0|"The sy is set up in a way that the emails get drafted... Only there the ag needs my input for a draft."
T|Patt|1|
T|Patt|2|Everything starts as a draft. ag prepare, human reviews and sends. Full automation is the vision, not the starting point. Trust is built incrementally: draft-first → rv-then-send → auto-send for trusted categories.
T|Patt|3|
T|Patt|4|yv status: ag execute directly. No draft-rv-send pipeline. ka's Read is the closest (read-only intelligence, no execution).
T|Patt|5|
T|Patt|0|"Each workspace has its unique and cool ds. Each mission control for each project will be designed separately, will have their own pages, their own page structure, and their own workflows."
T|Patt|1|
T|Patt|2|Workspaces aren't just data filters — they carry full visual identity (color theme, layout, custom pages). Partners get scoped logins that only see their workspace.
T|Patt|3|
T|Patt|4|yv status: nz and hb share the same glass-morphism ds. VentureSwitcher changes data, not aesthetics.
T|Patt|5|
K|Patt|0|"I can literally rv the draft rp here and send and edit from right here. I don't need to go to my em inbox anymore."
K|Patt|1|
K|Patt|2|Every decision and action happens inline — ap a post, send an em, merge a PR, rotate a key — w/o navigating away. The page is the tool.
K|Patt|3|
K|Patt|4|yv status: Mixed. Some dashboards have action buttons; most require navigation to different pages.
K|Patt|5|
K|Patt|6|---
K|Patt|7|
