T|NOT |5|---
T|NOT |6|
D|Deci|0|mc shd become yv's "hy" — a dedicated filter layer btw all 13 ag and the ce dashboard. Every ag output passes through mc before reaching any dashboard. mc decides: auto-handle, escalate to ce, or defer w/ nudge.
D|Deci|1|
D|Deci|0|yv currently has dv pushing directly to master. Change to: dv creates PR → qn runs automated QA (rc-doctor, lint, typecheck, tst) → if QA passes, escalates to ce Decision Queue → ce merges. This is non-negotiable for production code safety.
D|Deci|1|
D|Deci|0|All ag actions that have external side effects (sl posting, em sending, code merging, key rotation) must start as drafts requiring human approval. Only read-only actions (ka's Read, an queries) can execute autonomously. This puts yv on the trust-building trajectory.
D|Deci|1|
D|Deci|0|Replace the current scattered approval pattern (War Room tasks here, sl cn there, code elsewhere) w/ a single Decision Queue that aggregates everything needing ce attention. mc is the gatekeeper; the queue is the single source of truth for "what needs me."
D|Deci|1|
D|Deci|0|Give nz its own dark-fashion aesthetic and hb its own fintech palette. The glass-morphism sy stays as the shared foundation, but each vt gets unique accent colors, typography tweaks, and custom page layouts where appropriate. This is what LifeOS calls "each workspace designed separately w/ its own pages."
D|Deci|1|
D|Deci|2|---
D|Deci|3|
T|Part|0|Credit where it's due — yv is ahead of LifeOS in several areas:
T|Part|1|
T|Part|2|Actually built and deployed. LifeOS is 100% mockups — hardcoded data, no functionality. yv ships real code w/ CI/CD.
T|Part|3|
T|Part|4|Business domain depth. yv has: cr intelligence, merchandising, vt financials, GA4 an, Apify scraping, Facebook Graph ap, DeepSeek balance tracking. LifeOS is a personal productivity tool.
T|Part|5|
T|Part|6|ag specialization. yv's 13 ag are more specialized than LifeOS's ~12. yv has dedicated fi (fx), merchandising, and cr ag.
T|Part|7|
T|Part|8|sb maturity. yv has 49 migrations, production sb, real tk tracking w/ live DeepSeek balance. LifeOS mentions sb but has no migrations shown.
T|Part|9|
T|Part|10|CI/CD pipeline. yv has lint → typecheck → bd → tst → sec → dp to vc. LifeOS has no bd pipeline shown.
T|Part|11|
T|Part|12|Hermes ag integration. yv spawns real Hermes subprocesses w/ graph memory injection. LifeOS relies on its own ag runtime.
T|Part|13|
T|Part|14|---
T|Part|15|
T|Part|0|LifeOS's real innovation isn't any single page — it's the process and the ds philosophy:
T|Part|1|
T|Part|2|"I didn't show you a finished pd. None of this is built yet. I showed you a process."
T|Part|3|
T|Part|4|The process: brain dump → structure w/ ag → audit current sy → cast vision per page → PRDs → mockups → final pass → bd.
T|Part|5|
T|Part|6|The philosophy: every screen answers one question — how do I save the human's time and attention?
T|Part|7|
T|Part|8|yv was built feature-first ("let's add a cr dashboard, let's add an, let's add a war room"). LifeOS was built human-first ("what are the 7 things that actually need me?").
T|Part|9|
T|Part|10|The upgrade path for yv isn't "cp these pages." It's "adopt this philosophy" — then the pages will ds themselves.
T|Part|11|
T|Part|12|---
